    "\n",
    "This notebook demonstrated:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Mean-Variance Optimization**: Creating efficient portfolios using Modern Portfolio Theory\n",
    "2. **Hierarchical Risk Parity**: Machine learning-based allocation that doesn't require expected returns\n",
    "3. **Tax Loss Harvesting**: Identifying opportunities to harvest losses and save on taxes\n",
    "4. **Portfolio Backtesting**: Testing strategies with historical data\n",
    "5. **Tax-Efficient Withdrawals**: Optimizing retirement withdrawal sequences\n",
    "\n",
    "### Key Takeaways\n",
    "\n",
    "- **MVO** provides theoretically optimal portfolios but requires accurate return estimates\n",
    "- **HRP** is more robust to estimation errors and works well with just covariance data\n",
    "- **Tax Loss Harvesting** can add significant after-tax returns\n",
    "- **Backtesting** helps validate strategies before implementation\n",
    "- **Withdrawal sequencing** matters - generally withdraw from taxable → IRA → Roth"
